To reverse an array in Java, you can use the following algorithm:
1. Initialize two pointers, one at the start of the array (let's call it 'start') and the other at the end of the array (let's call it 'end').
2. Swap the elements at the 'start' and 'end' positions.
3. Increment the 'start' pointer and decrement the 'end' pointer.
4. Repeat steps 2 and 3 until the 'start' pointer is greater than or equal to the 'end' pointer.
5. The array will be reversed after executing the above steps.
Here's the Java code to implement the algorithm:
```java
public static void reverseArray(int[] arr) {
    int start = 0;
    int end = arr.length - 1;
    while (start < end) {
        int temp = arr[start];
        arr[start] = arr[end];
        arr[end] = temp;
        start++;
        end--;
    }
}
```
